description: Tetum (Tetun Indonesian: Bahasa Tetum; Portuguese) TÃ©tum is an Austronesian language spoken on the island of Timor. It is spoken in Belu Regency in Indonesian West Timor, and across the border in East Timor, where it is one of the two official languages.
